sdp/runner.log:330:{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-04-27T01:24:59.123Z","role":"user","content":"# Verification: Task T-002@20260427T001208Z\n\n**Task:** Implement Replicate rate-limit (429) and 5xx retry with exponential backoff bounded to 3 attempts, honoring `Retry-After`.\n**Tier:** T1\n\nYou are the VERIFY agent for this task. The LEAD agent has completed their work.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- `ReplicateClient.generate` wraps prediction submission in a retry loop<br/>- Retry on 429 and 5xx; do NOT retry on 4xx (other than 429)<br/>- Backoff: 5 s → 30 s → 5 min, capped at `Retry-After` if present and larger<br/>- Maximum 3 retries; after that raises `GenerationError`<br/>- Tests mock httpx-style responses and assert call counts + delays\n\n## Review Checklist\n\n1. **Review recent commits:**\n   ```bash\n   git log --oneline -5\n   git diff HEAD~3 --stat\n   ```\n\n2. **Review code changes:**\n   ```bash\n   git diff HEAD~3\n   ```\n\n4. **Check ESCALATIONS.md** for any flagged issues.\n\n5. **Run the test suite:**\n   ```bash\n   pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x\n   ```\n\n## Evaluation Criteria\n\nEvaluate the work against these five dimensions:\n\n1. **Correctness**: Does the output match the requirements/spec?\n2. **Completeness**: Are there gaps, missing edge cases, or unhandled scenarios?\n3. **Consistency**: Does the output follow established patterns and conventions?\n4. **Security**: Are there vulnerabilities, leaked secrets, or unsafe practices?\n5. **Quality**: Does the output meet the quality gates for this phase?\n\n## Output\n\nWrite your verification report and all findings to this exact path:\n`sdp/verification/t-002@20260427t001208z-verify.md`\nDo not use a different filename or directory.\n\nUse this format:\n\n```markdown\n# Verification Report — T-002@20260427T001208Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** [your agent name]\n**Date:** [today]\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** [list files reviewed]\n\n## Correctness\n[assessment]\n\n## Completeness\n[assessment]\n\n## Consistency\n[assessment]\n\n## Security\n[assessment]\n\n## Quality\n[assessment]\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] [Issue — severity: blocking/minor]\n\n## Verdict: [PASS | PASS WITH NOTES | FAIL]\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\n[specific items to address]\n```\n\nCommit the verification report.\n\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\n\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Ensure this path is used on both standalone and federated modes..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that exercises startup and verifies identity persistence between boots..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Re-run pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x after wiring the startup path..\n"}
sdp/runner.log:378:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-27T01:25:42.116Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777253142116_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-002@20260427t001208z-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-002@20260427T001208Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-26\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_replicate.py`\n- `tests/test_generation_replicate_retry.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation correctly handles HTTP 429 and 5xx retries with the specified exponential backoff schedule (5s, 30s, 300s). It honors the `Retry-After` header when it is larger than the scheduled backoff. Non-retryable 4xx errors correctly raise a `GenerationError` immediately.\n\n## Completeness\nThe retry logic is complete according to the acceptance criteria. It covers the initial attempt plus up to 3 retries (4 total attempts). The `raise_for_response` helper correctly parses the `Retry-After` header from httpx-style response objects.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows the established patterns in the project, using clear exception hierarchies (`GenerationError` as the base for surfaced errors, `ReplicateAPIError` for internal HTTP-level handling). The tests use a `_Recorder` pattern consistent with other timing-sensitive tests in the codebase.\n\n## Security\nNo security issues or leaked credentials found. The client uses an `api_token` that is passed in but not logged or stored unsafely in the provided code.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-documented with docstrings explaining the retry policy. Tests are comprehensive, covering happy paths, various error status codes, `Retry-After` overrides, and the budget exhaustion scenario. `ruff check` passes cleanly.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nImplementation of the retry surface is solid and verified. Ready for T-001 to implement the full submission/polling/download flow using this surface.\n"}}
