f the full submit→poll→download flow in `ReplicateClient.generate` is correct and aligns with the requirements. It successfully resolved the previous stub into a functional end-to-end generator. The `_download_output` helper handles various Replicate output formats (URL strings, lists of URLs, file readers, and raw bytes) as required. The `GenerationResult` (returned as a dictionary) correctly includes `audio_bytes`, `model_used`, `prediction_id`, and `latency_ms`.\\n\\n## Completeness\\nThe task is complete. All branches for output resolution are implemented and tested. The `GenerationClient` protocol was updated to ensure structural parity across `ReplicateClient`, `ModalClient`, and the `LocalAdaClient` stub. Edge cases like empty output lists or unsupported output types are handled with clear `GenerationError` exceptions.\\n\\n## Consistency\\nThe changes follow established patterns for client implementation and testing in the `senseweave` subsystem. The return type update to `dict[str, Any]` was applied consistently across all generation clients. The use of `audio_bytes` instead of `image_bytes` is consistent with the audio-focused nature of the `cypherclaw-musicgen` project, despite the minor naming variation in the initial task prompt.\\n\\n## Security\\nNo security vulnerabilities were introduced. API tokens are handled through the constructor and not logged. The download process uses `urllib.request` with a timeout bounded by `self._timeout_sec`.\\n\\n## Quality\\nThe code quality is high. Docstrings are informative, and the implementation is modular. Tests are comprehensive, covering retry logic, polling timeouts, download branch coverage, and end-to-end wiring.\\n\\n## Issues Found\\n- [x] (Resolved) Typo in task description: The prompt mentioned \\\"image bytes\\\", but the project is audio-centric. The implementation uses `audio_bytes`, which is correct for the CypherClaw context and consistent with `ModalClient`.\\n- [x] (Verified) Hardening Check: `bootstrap_identity()` was verified to be correctly called in `daemon.py`, `cypherclaw_daemon.py`, and `sample_capture_daemon.py` before any identity-dependent logic (like `FirstBootAnnouncer`). Persistence and wiring are covered by passing integration tests in `tests/test_first_boot.py` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py`.\\n\\n## Verdict: PASS\\n\\n## Notes for Lead Agent\\nExcellent work wiring the end-to-end Replicate flow. The `_download_output` utility is particularly robust. The consistency across all backends ensures the orchestrator can swap backends without modification.\\n\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T03:00:23.612Z\",\"tool_id\":\"write_file_1777258823585_0\",\"status\":\"success\"}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T03:00:25.499Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"I will now commit the verification report for task T-001 to the repository.\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T03:00:25.533Z\",\"tool_name\":\"run_shell_command\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1777258825533_0\",\"parameters\":{\"command\":\"git add sdp/verification/t-001@20260427t001208zc-verify.md && git commit -m \\\"verify(T-001@20260427T001208Zc): PASS\\\" && git status\",\"description\":\"Committing the verification report.\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T03:00:25.760Z\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1777258825533_0\",\"status\":\"success\",\"output\":\"[feat/graceful-degradation e8c9a65] verify(T-001@20260427T001208Zc): PASS\\n 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+), 34 deletions(-)\\nOn branch feat/graceful-degradation\\nYour branch is ahead of 'origin/feat/graceful-degradation' by 470 commits.\\n  (use \\\"git push\\\" to publish your local commits)\\n\\nChanges not staged for commit:\\n  (use \\\"git add <file>...\\\" to update what will be committed)\\n  (use \\\"git restore <file>...\\\" to discard changes in working directory)\\n        modified:   sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_2026